SUBROUTINES
    ttyname(3)   	- look up the filename of a terminal device

INVOCATION
    char  *ttyname( desc )
      int  desc;

EXPLANATION
    The argument <desc> must be a file descriptor for a character
    device. This routine returns a pointer to the filename within
    "/dev" which is associated with that file descriptor. For
    example, the command tty(1) is almost as simple as
    "puts( ttyname(0) )".

    The string space for the filename is static storage within
    ttyname(3), it is overwritten by subsequent calls.

RESULTS
    NULL : No filename found in /dev.
    o/w  : Pointer to string name of device.

FILES
    /dev/*

REFERENCES
    tty(1), fstat(2), isatty(2), ctermid(3)
